---
description: Instructions for when to not use the terminal
globs: ["**/*.ts", "**/*.d.ts", "**/*.js"]
---

Good:
- Building the code and ensuring the `dist/` output is correct
- Examining logs to find out what went wrong

Bad:
- Using replacements with terminal utilities like `sed` rather than manually editing the files. You can't use bulk find-and-replace. Instead make those changes manually.